  .slide
    h2 Why all of these stats? <br>I thought this was Oral Comm!
    ul
      li Setting the Stage
      li Need to 
        a(href="http://dictionary.reference.com/browse/perception") perceive
        | &nbsp;correctly
        ul
          li Mine: "Our 'view' of the world, interactions and communications"
      li A form of 
         a(href="http://www.arts.ualberta.ca/igel/igel2004/Proceedings/Bartsch.pdf") Emotive Communication
         ul
            li Book: Words that sound as if they're describing something when they are really announcing the speaker's attitude
      li How all of this relates back to American Politics

    .speaker
      ul
        li Why stats?
        li Perceive What?
        li Form of Emotive Comm?

  .slide
    h2 Guatemalan Elections: Perception in Communication
    ul
      li Polital Officals usually Spanish
      li Indigenous people can vote
      li Wealth vs Power
